# Templ ‚Äî Registry structure

Copy-paste **component library** (`github.com/fastygo/templ`). Not an application shell ‚Äî consuming apps (e.g. Blank) own routes, fixtures, and chrome.

On-disk index: [`README.md`](../../README.md), [`docs/README.md`](../../docs/README.md).

```
utils/              # shared Go helpers ‚Äî Cn, Compose, ARIA, tags, form recipes
ui/                 # primitives ‚Äî button/, stack/, form/, dialog/, ‚Ä¶
  <brick>/
    <brick>.spec.md
    <brick>.variants.json   # target layout (migrate inline Variants here)
    <brick>.data.json       # showcase fixtures (optional)
    <brick>.templ
    <brick>.tsx             # React port (optional)
components/         # composites ‚Äî card/, sheet/, nav/, alert/, ‚Ä¶
  <brick>/            # same file set as ui/
components.json     # shadcn-style registry manifest
examples/           # optional local preview ‚Äî NOT copy-pasted with bricks
  page.templ        # document shell for preview
  demo.templ        # RegistryDemo composition
  cmd/server/       # minimal HTTP preview
  ui/blocks/        # full demo scaffolds (home, dashboard)
  web/static/       # preview tokens, CSS, ui8kit bundle
.validate/          # spec validator, blockgen
.ui8px/policy/      # Tailwind class policy for registry + examples
docs/               # long-lived architecture, ARIA, onboarding, publishing docs
```

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `utils/` | **Only** shared helpers ‚Äî no brick markup |
| `ui/` | Primitives ‚Äî props, variants, children; framework-neutral by default |
| `components/` | Composites ‚Äî multi-part bricks (`parts[]` in spec) |
| `ui/*/facade.templ`, `components/facade.templ` | Re-export facades ‚Äî prefer `@ui.*`, `@cmp.*` in examples |
| `examples/` | Preview server, demo copy, block scaffolds ‚Äî app-like but not shipped |
| `examples/templ/ui/blocks/<name>/` | Wireframe scaffolds: `props.go`, `page.templ`, generated `page_gen.go` (fixture/variant JSON lives in `examples/data/`) |

## Per-brick contract

Colocate under `ui/<brick>/` or `components/<brick>/`:

1. `{brick}.spec.md` ‚Äî machine-readable API (authoritative)
2. `{brick}.variants.json` ‚Äî CVA class map (shared target for Go + React)
3. `{brick}.data.json` ‚Äî showcase props + sample slot content (optional)
4. `{brick}.templ` ‚Äî Go implementation
5. `{brick}.tsx` ‚Äî React implementation when dual-stack port exists

## Import shape

```templ
import "github.com/fastygo/templ/ui"
import cmp "github.com/fastygo/templ/components"
```

Granular imports (`ui/button`) remain valid for copy-paste consumers. **Inside this repo**, examples and new bricks should prefer facades unless testing a single package.

## Examples vs library

| Layer | Library (`ui/`, `components/`) | Examples (`examples/`) |
|-------|-------------------------------|-------------------------|
| Demo copy | forbidden in bricks | `*.data.json`, block `props.go` |
| Tokens / theme | not shipped | `examples/web/static/css/tokens.css` |
| `@ui8kit/aria` bundle | opt-in via `Behavior` / `DataUI8Kit` | preview-only `ui8kit.js` |
| HTTP server | none | `examples/cmd/server` |

## Forbidden

- App routes, locale fixtures, or site chrome inside `ui/` or `components/`.
- Hard-coded product copy inside registry bricks (use `examples/` or consumer app).
- Deep imports in docs/examples when demonstrating public API (`@ui.Button`, not ad-hoc forks).
- `utility-prop` style APIs (`gap=`, `flex=` as props) ‚Äî use `Class` + ui8px.
- Behavior hooks enabled by default on bricks (`Behavior`, `DataUI8Kit` must default off).

## Adding a brick

1. Add `ui/<brick>/` or `components/<brick>/` with `*.spec.md` from [`.validate/docs/component.spec.template.md`](../../.validate/docs/component.spec.template.md).
2. Add `*.variants.json`; wire `ButtonClasses`-style helpers to `Compose`.
3. Implement `*.templ`; run `bun run generate`.
4. Add showcase to spec + optional `*.data.json`.
5. Extend `examples/demo.templ` or a block under `examples/templ/ui/blocks/` when a visual preview is needed.
6. Run validation ‚Äî see **`templ-validation-testing.mdc`**.

Do not add durable docs or planning notes under `.project`; use `docs/` for
human documentation and `.cursor/rules/` for agent-facing operating rules.
